        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 10:18PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 1017 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Neola, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Neola around 1025 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
